article.headline: N. Dakota St. 42, Lafayette 6
article.story: FARGO, N.D. -- Brock Jensen and Warren Holloway combined for two long touchdown passes and North Dakota State breezed past Lafayette 42-6 Saturday night in the season opener for both teams. Jensen hit Holloway for a 67-yard score 11 seconds into the game. D.J. McNorton ran for three touchdowns, all in the first half, as the Bison built a 28-0 lead before the break. Holloway caught a 57-yard touchdown pass from Jensen in the fourth quarter. Jensen was 15 of 22 for 197 yards -- 147 of them to Holloway. Ryan O'Neil threw a 6-yard TD pass to Mitchell Bennett for the Leopards' only points. There were no turnovers in the game.
